## Rules {#rules heading="Rules"}

### Initial Infection Rule {#initial-infection-rule heading="Initial Infection Rule"}

-   rule = initial_infect_r
    -   Uses if_close_avg and query_vertices
-   Automatically infects as mild
-   **Need to implement random sampling from lognormal distribution with
    mean=1.621 and sigma=0.418. Right now it\'s just a random int**

### Increment infected days {#increment-infected-days heading="Increment infected days"}

-   rule = increment_r
-   adds 1 to daysIm and substracts 1 from symptomsIm

### Check if it\'s time to show symptoms {#check-if-its-time-to-show-symptoms heading="Check if it's time to show symptoms"}

-   rule = checkI0
    -   Uses is_symptom_day and q_im

### Appearance of symptoms (mild infected) {#appearance-of-symptoms-mild-infected heading="Appearance of symptoms (mild infected)"}

-   rule = symptoms_r
    -   Removes edges from Im showing symptoms *except* for \"home\"
        edges

### Check if infected for 20 days {#check-if-infected-for-20-days heading="Check if infected for 20 days"}

-   rule = i20

### Flip for recovery {#flip-for-recovery heading="Flip for recovery"}

-   rule = recoveryFlip
-   Depends on when the Im started showing symptoms

### Recovery {#recovery heading="Recovery"}

-   rule = recoverMildApp

## Schedules {#schedules heading="Schedules"}

-   initial_infection_sched
    -   A schedule for infecting an initial person given a graph
        populated with nodes and edges
-   sched_rec
    -   A schedule for looping through mildly infected people,
        incrementing infected days, starting symptoms, flipping for
        recovery, and recovering appropriately

# Model steps (may be incorrect) {#model-steps-may-be-incorrect heading="Model steps (may be incorrect)"}

## Initialization {#initialization heading="Initialization"}

-   Create nodes, assign ages according to age distributions
-   All nodes start in \"S\" state with 0 days infected
-   Create edges and assign weights (need to clarify this procedure,
    code is
    [here](https://github.com/scabini/COmplexVID-19/blob/master/comunities.py){.external-link
    aria-label-position="top"
    aria-label="https://github.com/scabini/COmplexVID-19/blob/master/comunities.py"
    rel="noopener" target="_blank"})
-   Calculate the average per-node degree of the graph.
    -   While current infected [$<$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded}
        initial infected (default 1), look at random node. If node has
        average_graph_degree - 1 [$<=$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded}
        degree [$<=$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded}
        average_graph_degree + 1 infect that node

## Loop {#loop heading="Loop"}

-   For all [$I_{a}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} nodes:
    -   +1 to days infected. If this results in [$>=$]{.math
        .math-inline .is-loaded} 8 infected days, flip a coin for
        recovery
        -   If succesful, recovered (remove all edges connected to node)
    -   For all [$I_{m}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} nodes:
        -   +1 to days infected.
            -   If this results in started symptoms. Remove all edges
                except for \"home\" (simulating home quarantine)
                -   AND 20% flip of being diagnosed
            -   If [$>=10$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected days
                and showing symptoms. Flip a coin with prob
                [$\frac{1}{20 - \text{symptom\_start\_day}}$]{.math
                .math-inline .is-loaded} for recovery (uniform chance of
                recovery while symptoms showing)
            -   If [$>=20$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected
                days, recovered (remove all edges)
    -   For all [$I_{s}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} nodes:
        -   +1 to days infected
            -   If results in started symptoms, +1 occupied hospital
                beds and +1 diagnosed. AND hospital isolation (remove
                all edges)
            -   If [$>=20$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected
                days, flip coin for death (15% over 5 days)
                -   if dead, -1 occupied beds
            -   If [$>=25$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected
                days, recovered and -1 occupied beds
    -   For all [$I_{c}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} nodes:
        -   +1 to days infected
            -   If results in started symptoms, +1 to occupied UTI beds
                (intensive care), +1 diagnosed. AND hospital isolation
                (remove all edges)
            -   If [$>=21$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected
                days, flip coin for death (50% over 4 days)
                -   If head, -1 occupied UTI beds
            -   If [$>=25$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded} infected
                days, -1 occupied UTI beds and recovered
    -   For all edges between \"S\" and any infect node:
        -   flip a coin according to edge weight
            -   if succesful, flip a coin for assignment to infection
                state \[[$I_{a}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded},
                [$I_{m}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded},
                [$I_{s}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded},
                [$I_{c}$]{.math .math-inline .is-loaded}\] = \[0.3,
                0.55, 0.1, 0.05\]. And choose day symptoms will start
                (2-14 with log-normal (Weibull) distribution with
                mean=6.4 days and stddev=2.3).
                -   If assigned to [$I_{s}$]{.math .math-inline
                    .is-loaded} or [$I_{c}$]{.math .math-inline
                    .is-loaded}, after choosing symptom start day set
                    symptom floor at 9 and 8 respectively (can\'t be
                    lower than this)
    -   On \"action\" days (March 24 and May 25)
        -   remove layers assigned to day as removed
            -   March 24 = transport, school, church
            -   May 25 = work
        -   replace layers assigned to day as restored
            -   Currently none
        -   For each removed layer, boost the \"home\" layer weights by
            20% (so on march 24th, removed 3 layers and home layer
            weights get multiplied by 1.6)
